          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Ans. is c, i.e. 3.5 kgRef. Dutta Obs. 9/e, p 68Estimation of fetal weight can be done using Johnson formula:If station of head below ischial spine x 155If fetal head is at or above ischial spine- x 155 Here fetal head is at - 2, i.e. above ischial spine, so it will be (35 - 12) x 155 = 3.5 kg.Also Know:USG measurement of fetal weight =Shephard formula =Log10 EFW(gm)=1.2508+-(0.002646xACxBPD)Hadlock formula =Log10 EFW(gm)=1.3596-0.00386(ACxFL)+0.0064(HC)+0.00061(BPDxAC)+0.0425(AC)+0.0174(FL)",
