          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. D. Termination of pregnancyPatient presents with the characteristics of Severe Hypertension indicating delivery.Induction of labor is the best suited management of choice.Magnesium Sulfate prophylaxis should be provided to prevent the onset of seizures.Severe pre-eclampsia can be characterized as:* Pulmonary edema* BP >160/110* Fetal growth restriction* >-3+ proteinuria* Complaints of convulsion, headache, upper abdominal pain, oliguria and visual disturbances* Increased levels of serum creatinine, serum transaminase or presence of thrombocytopenia",
