          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Postpaum Mood Disorders Post paum blues Occur within first few days and resolve by 2 weeks (50-60 %) Due to sudden loss of progesterones. Characterised by mild mood swings, irritability, anxiety, decreased concentration, insomnia , tearfullness, crying spells85% of women for a sho time in the immediate postpaum period. Post paum Depression Occurs in first 3-6 months (10-15%) insomnia, anxiety, low self woh, unable to care for and bond with baby, Post paum Psychosis Within first 2-3 months (<1%) severe insomnia, rapid mood swings, anxiety, psychomotor restlessness, delusions and hallucinations",
