          "explanation": "Ans. is b i.e. Both veex In twins most common lie of both the fetus at term is longitudinal.deg Rarest lie is both the twins transverse.deg Presentations : Both veex (Most common) 60% Veex (1st) - Breech (1Ind) 20% Breech (1st) - Veex (11nd) 10% Both Breech 8 - 10% Note : Interlocking of twins is a rare complication seen in twins with 1st Breech presentation and Ind veex presentation."
