          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "PCOS is associated with elevated LH and mildly elevated testosterone. In case of stromal hypehecosis, though testosterone is elevated and LH is normal. Markedly elevated testosterone > 2 ng/ml is suggestive of tumor. Ref: Essentials of Gynaecology by Lakshmi Seshadri, Edition 1, page - 254."
