          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Colostrum is very rich in proteins, vitamin A and sodium chloride, but contains lower amounts of carbohydrates, lipids, and potassium than normal milk. Colostrum contains immunoglobulins such as IgA, IgG, and IgM."
