          "explanation": "Ans. is 'b' i.e., FSH is elevated * A very high FSH would indicate a testicular cause, (hypergonadotropic hypogonadism)* A very low FSH would indicate pretesticular (hypothalamic/pituitary) cause.* A normal FSH would indicate a posttesticular cause.",
