          "explanation": "Ans. is d, i.e. Osteitis pubisRef: Telinde 9th/ed, p1057-8; Textbook of Gynae, Sheila Balakrishnan 1st/ed, p329Marshall-Marchetti-Krantz (MMK) procedure, involves the attachment of the periurethral tissue to the symphysis pubuis.In approximately, 3% of patients undergoing the procedure, osteitis pubis develops.",
