          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "GnRH analogues used for 6months reduces the tumour size by 50-80%. This treatment in premenopausal women, young women and infeility caused by cornual fibroid eliminates the need for surgery. RU 486(Mifepristone) 10-25mg daily for 3months causes amenorrhoea and shrinkage of tumour by 50%. Danazol 400-800mg daily for 3-6months reduces the size of the tumour. However side effects includes hirsutism as well as costly. Reference: Textbook of shaw,15th edition,page 359",
