          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'b' i.e., 3 or more consecutive losses < 20 weeks * Recurrent miscarriage, habitual abortion, or recurrent pregnancy loss (RPL) is three or more consecutive pregnancy losses at less than (or equal to) 20 weeks of gestation or with a fetal weight of <500 grams.* It affects approximately 1% to 2% of women",
