          "text": "25 year old female patient is referred from a PHC with history of expanding vulvar mass, during first hour post partum. She delivered normally and without perineal laceration. She complains of severe pain. On examination her BP is 90/40 mmHg, pulse = 130bpm and no fever. what is your approach in treatment of patient",
