          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "The increase in cardiac output does not cause increase in BP. This is due to massive fall in peripheral vascular resistance due to smooth muscle relaxant propeies of progesterone. Reference : Dutta's Textbook of Obstetrics 7th edition page 53",
