          "explanation": "Ans. A. CMVManifestations of CMV in the neonates include focal or generalized organ involvement. These include petechiae, hepatosplenomegaly, jaundice, microcephaly, IUGR, Chorioretinitis and inguinal hernia in male infants.",
          "hint": "Topic: Medical & Surgical Illness Complication Pregnancy"
